\pard\f0\fs28  Sect. TRIADENIA (Spach) R. Keller. Dwarf, glabrous, microphyllous shrubs, without black glands. Leaves opposite. Flowers terminating long or short shoots, heterostylous. Sepals entire. Petals with entire, ligulate, nectariferous appendage. Stamen fascicles 3, with filaments united for more than ½ their length, alternating with 3 fleshy fasciclodes. Fruit dry. Seeds slightly carinate, with fleshy caruncle.
