\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 7. H. aciferum} (W. Greuter) N.K.B. Robson,{\i  Feddes Repert. }{\b 74}: 23 (1967) ({\i Elodes acifera} W. Greuter). Low, procumbent shrub. Leaves 5-12 mm, narrowly linear-spathulate, coriaceous, somewhat glaucous, not imbricate. Flowers (1-)3, pedicellate. Sepals suberect, elliptical. Petals c. 9 mm, deciduous. Stamens persistent. Ovary with 2 ovules in each loculus. {\i Calcareous rocks near the sea. • S.W. Kriti.} Cr.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 8. H. aegypticum} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 784 (1753) ({\i Triadenia maritima} (Sieber) Boiss.). Low, spreading shrub. Leaves 3-10 mm, elliptical to narrowly oblong, coriaceous, glaucous, often crowded and imbricate. Flowers solitary, sessile or subsessile. Sepals erect, oblong. Petals 8-14 mm, persistent. Stamens persistent. Ovary with numerous ovules in each loculus.{\i  Cliffs and rocks near the sea. Islands of C. & E. Mediterranean from Sardegna to Kriti.} Cr Gr Sa Si. ({\i N. Africa}.)
\par

