\pard\f0\fs28  Sect. HAPLOPHYLLOIDES Stefanov. Glabrous dwarf shrubs. Black glands confined to leaf-apex and sepal- and petal-margins. Stem 4-angled. Leaves opposite, subcoriaceous. Flowers few, in cymes. Petals and stamens persistent. Stamen-fascicles and styles 3. Capsule with longitudinal vittae. Seeds papillose.
\par

