\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 13. H. haplophylloides} Halácsy & Bald.,{\i  Verh. Zool.-Bot. Ges. Wien }{\b 42}: 576 (1893). Stems up to 25 cm, straggling, branching and rooting at the base. Leaves 12-28 mm, oblong-linear to elliptic-linear, with apical black gland. Cymes 3- to 5-flowered. Sepals black-glandular-ciliate or -denticulate. Petals with small, sessile, marginal black glands.{\i  Mountain woods and rocks. • S. Albania.} Al.
\par

