\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 15. H. linarioides} Bosse, {\i Allgem. Gartenz.}{\b  3}: 99 (1835) ({\i H. alpestre} Steven, {\i H. repens} auct., non L.). Stems (5-)8-17(-30) cm, erect from creeping and rooting base, glabrous. Leaves on main stem (5-)8-14 mm, linear to narrowly elliptical, without apical gland, glabrous, usually with deflexed margin; leaves on axillary shoots smaller and crowded. Inflorescence subspicate, or with lowest branches somewhat elongated. Sepals with or without marginal black glands. Petals often red-tinged or red-veined. Anthers yellow. {\i Mountain rocks and grassland. C. part of Balkan peninsula; Krym.} Bu Gr Ju Rs (K).
